Reasoning: The paper deals with the decidability and enumeration of properties of k-automatic sequences, which are sequences generated by finite automata. This falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses Pisot numeration systems, which are related to number theory and combinatorics (cs.FL). The use of automata and Pisot numeration systems also suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and logic (cs.LO). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the study of formal languages and automata theory (cs.CC).
